    direction: "Apply a reinforcement learning approach (e.g., Deep Q‑Network) where the agent selects the next operation to schedule based on state features such as remaining processing time and machine availability."
    source_refs[0]:
    approach: Greedy scheduling with priority queue for machine availability
    code: "import heapq\nimport time\n\ndef solve(jobs):\n    # Initialize machine availability\n    num_machines = max(max(op['machine'] for op in job) for job in jobs) + 1 if jobs else 0\n    machine_availability = [0] * num_machines\n    \n    # Create a list to track the current operation index for each job\n    job_ops = [0] * len(jobs)\n    \n    # Priority queue: (next_available_time, machine_index)\n    machine_queue = []\n    for machine in range(num_machines):\n        heapq.heappush(machine_queue, (0, machine))\n    \n    # Track scheduled operations\n    scheduled = [[op.copy() for op in job] for job in jobs]\n    \n    # While there are operations left to schedule\n    while any(job_ops[job_idx] < len(jobs[job_idx]) for job_idx in range(len(jobs))):\n        # Find all operations that can be scheduled next\n        available_ops = []\n        for job_idx in range(len(jobs)):\n            op_idx = job_ops[job_idx]\n            if op_idx < len(jobs[job_idx]):\n                op = jobs[job_idx][op_idx]\n                machine = op['machine']\n                \n                # Check if previous operation in job is completed\n                if op_idx == 0 or scheduled[job_idx][op_idx-1]['start'] + scheduled[job_idx][op_idx-1]['duration'] <= machine_availability[machine]:\n                    available_ops.append((job_idx, op_idx, machine))\n        \n        if not available_ops:\n            # No operations can be scheduled yet, advance time to next machine availability\n            if machine_queue:\n                next_time, machine = heapq.heappop(machine_queue)\n                machine_availability[machine] = next_time\n            continue\n        \n        # Schedule the operation with earliest possible start time\n        best_op = None\n        best_start = float('inf')\n        \n        for job_idx, op_idx, machine in available_ops:\n            # Calculate earliest possible start time\n            prev_op_finish = 0\n            if op_idx > 0:\n                prev_op_finish = scheduled[job_idx][op_idx-1]['start'] + scheduled[job_idx][op_idx-1]['duration']\n            \n            start_time = max(prev_op_finish, machine_availability[machine])\n            \n            if start_time < best_start:\n                best_start = start_time\n                best_op = (job_idx, op_idx, machine)\n        \n        if best_op:\n            job_idx, op_idx, machine = best_op\n            op = jobs[job_idx][op_idx]\n            \n            # Calculate actual start time\n            prev_op_finish = 0\n            if op_idx > 0:\n                prev_op_finish = scheduled[job_idx][op_idx-1]['start'] + scheduled[job_idx][op_idx-1]['duration']\n            \n            start_time = max(prev_op_finish, machine_availability[machine])\n            \n            # Schedule the operation\n            scheduled[job_idx][op_idx]['start'] = start_time\n            job_ops[job_idx] += 1\n            \n            # Update machine availability\n            machine_availability[machine] = start_time + op['duration']\n            heapq.heappush(machine_queue, (machine_availability[machine], machine))\n    \n    return scheduled"
